39. 3. sed tuit...lntellegl (non) potest. The connection of thought, misunderstood by many, is as follows: Before the creation of the world and the heavenly bodies there was en eternity without beginning or division into periods3 but of its duration (lit. of what sort it was in respect to duration, spolio) we can have no conception. We can conceive only measurable and limited time; but this was a thing impossible before the heavenly bodies existed, by whose movements lime is measured and di· vided.— The negation before polest is indispensahle. Comp. Arist. Phys. IV, 11 ; Sext. Emp. Pyrrh. hypot. 111, 140 f. Victoria. ad Cic. De Invent. 1, p. 79, Orelli.
